          "snippet": "NHS infrastructure improvements are being held back by the outdated PDC charge, and this could impede government attempts to \"build back better\". Howard Davis looks at the state of healthcare infrastructure.\n\nToo often, government policy ignores social infrastructure when setting out investment plans. But the last year has shown the critical importance of the NHS, and therefore, its infrastructure to the economy.\n\nWhile direct spending on NHS capital has increased, the government has also shut down other methods for the NHS to fund health infrastructure.",
